    {
      "id": "node-prompt-job-application-prepare",
      "type": "prompt",
      "title": "Cover Letter Prompt",
      "description": "Build a grounded create cover letter prompt.",
      "position": {
        "x": 880,
        "y": 240
      },
      "inputs": [
        "bundle",
        "context"
      ],
      "outputs": [
        "prompt",
        "images"
      ],
      "config": {
        "prompt": {
          "template": "You are an expert career writer drafting a tailored cover letter for a specific candidate, role, and organisation. Use ONLY the data provided in the bundle below.\n\nPerson context JSON: {{bundle.personContext}}\nJob listing context JSON: {{bundle.jobContext}}\nOrganisation context JSON: {{bundle.organizationContext}}\nPlatform context JSON: {{bundle.platformContext}}\nGeneration request JSON: {{bundle.generationRequest}}\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON with this exact schema (no extra keys, no code fences):\n{\"coverLetter\":{\"subject\":\"\",\"bodyMarkdown\":\"\",\"bodyText\":\"\",\"language\":\"\"},\"applicationNotes\":[\"\"],\"missingInformation\":[\"\"],\"confidence\":0}\n\nContent rules:\n1. Language. Detect the language of jobContext.listing and write the entire letter in that language. Echo the BCP-47 tag in coverLetter.language. Fall back to platformContext.preferredLanguage or \"en\".\n2. Subject. <= 80 characters, includes the role title.\n3. Length and structure. 250-350 words, four paragraphs:\n   - Hook. One paragraph that opens with a concrete statement of interest in the role and the organisation, citing a specific fact from organizationContext (mission, product, recent harvestProfile/valueCatalog item) - never generic praise.\n   - Why this candidate fits. One paragraph mapping 2-3 candidate experiences from personContext.cvs[*] or personContext.linkedRecords to listing.requirements or listing.responsibilities. Quantify impact when source data permits. Prefer matches with jobContext.lexicon.selectedTechnologyTerms.\n   - Why this organisation. One paragraph showing motivation tied to a real organisation fact and connecting it to the candidate trajectory or values from personContext.person.\n   - Close. One paragraph: confirm availability for an interview, mention attached CV, sign off with full name and optional contact (phone, email, linkedinUrl) only if present in personContext.person.\n4. Salutation. Address a named contact from organizationContext.linkedPersons or organizationContext.linkedEmails when one is available; otherwise use a neutral form. Never invent names.\n5. Tone. Professional, direct, specific. No marketing fluff, no clichés (\"team player\", \"hit the ground running\"), no emojis, no ALL CAPS.\n6. Consistency. bodyMarkdown is the canonical body; bodyText is the same content as plain text (no Markdown syntax). Both must agree.\n7. Grounding. Never claim experience, employers, education, technologies, certifications, languages, or achievements not in the provided context.\n8. applicationNotes. 1-4 bullets explaining tailoring choices.\n9. missingInformation. Concrete data points whose absence weakened the letter.\n10. confidence. Self-assessment 0..1.\n11. Output JSON only. No markdown outside bodyMarkdown. No code fences. No commentary."
        }
      }
    },
    {
